This phase migrates the two most visible output components - DenialBox and TestResultBox - from manual ANSI escape codes to rich_rust Panel renderables. These are the "hero" components that users see most frequently.

### Why This Phase is P1 (High Priority)

1. **Highest Visibility**: DenialBox is shown every time a command is blocked - most seen output
2. **Complex Rendering**: Current code has 800+ lines of manual box drawing - high value replacement
3. **Validates Architecture**: Successfully migrating these proves the Console abstraction works
4. **User Feedback**: Premium-looking denial messages immediately improve perceived quality

### Key Files Modified

- `src/output/denial.rs` - Rewrite render methods to use Panel
- `src/output/test.rs` - Rewrite TestResultBox to use Panel
- `src/hook.rs` - Update print_colorful_warning() to use new DenialBox

### Technical Details

**DenialBox → Panel mapping:**
- Box borders → BoxStyle (rounded for normal, double for critical, heavy for high)
- ANSI colors → Markup syntax [bold red], [cyan], etc.
- Custom padding → Panel.padding((1, 2))
- Severity colors → Border style color based on severity

**TestResultBox → Panel mapping:**
- WOULD BE BLOCKED → Panel with red border, heavy style
- WOULD BE ALLOWED → Panel with green border, rounded style
- Confidence bar → Custom renderer using Unicode blocks

### Code Pattern Example

```rust
// OLD (manual ANSI):
writeln!(output, "\x1b[31m╭{}╮\x1b[0m", "─".repeat(width));

// NEW (rich_rust):
Panel::from_text(content)
    .title("[bold] DCG [/]")
    .border_style(Style::parse("red").unwrap())
    .box_style(BoxStyle::rounded())
```

### Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] DenialBox renders using rich_rust Panel
- [ ] TestResultBox renders using rich_rust Panel
- [ ] Visual output matches or exceeds current quality
- [ ] No ANSI escape codes manually generated
- [ ] All denial.rs and test.rs tests pass
- [ ] Hook mode still outputs JSON to stdout correctly
