 {"id":"bd-2jp9","title":"P4.1: Enhance doctor command with styled check results","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-19T21:11:46.053589798Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-21T18:24:35.733975605Z","closed_at":"2026-01-21T18:24:35.733869675Z","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2jp9","depends_on_id":"bd-2loz","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-19T21:12:16.112195399Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}],"comments":[{"id":53,"issue_id":"bd-2jp9","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"## Task: Enhance doctor command with styled check results

### What to Do

Redesign `dcg doctor` output to use rich_rust components for clearer health check reporting.

### Current Output

```
dcg doctor
✓ Configuration file found
✓ Packs directory exists
✗ Pack 'kubernetes' has syntax error
✓ Hook mode test passed
```

### Target Output

Using rich_rust Panel and styled text:
```
╭─────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│  🏥 dcg Health Check                        │
╰─────────────────────────────────────────────╯

Configuration
  [green]✓[/] Configuration file found at ~/.config/dcg/config.yaml
  [green]✓[/] Packs directory exists (15 packs loaded)

Pack Validation
  [green]✓[/] filesystem_critical: 12 patterns, valid
  [green]✓[/] git_safety: 8 patterns, valid
  [red]✗[/] kubernetes: Syntax error in pattern 'kubectl_delete'
        [dim]→ Invalid regex at position 23[/]

Hook Integration
  [green]✓[/] Claude Code hook test passed
  [yellow]![/] Shell integration not detected
        [dim]→ Add to .bashrc: eval "$(dcg init bash)"[/]

Summary: [yellow]2 warnings[/], [red]1 error[/]
```

### Implementation

```rust
pub fn run_doctor(config: &Config) -> DoctorReport {
    let mut report = DoctorReport::new();

    // Run checks
    report.add_check(check_config());
    report.add_check(check_packs());
    report.add_check(check_hook());

    #[cfg(feature = "rich-output")]
    eprintln!("{}", report.render_rich());

    #[cfg(not(feature = "rich-output"))]
    eprintln!("{}", report.render_plain());

    report
}

impl DoctorReport {
    #[cfg(feature = "rich-output")]
    fn render_rich(&self) -> String {
        use rich_rust::prelude::*;

        let mut output = Panel::from_text("[bold cyan]🏥 dcg Health Check[/]")
            .box_style(BoxStyle::rounded())
            .to_string();

        for section in &self.sections {
            output.push_str(&format!("\n[bold]{}[/]\n", section.name));
            for check in &section.checks {
                let (icon, color) = match check.status {
                    CheckStatus::Pass => ("✓", "green"),
                    CheckStatus::Warn => ("!", "yellow"),
                    CheckStatus::Fail => ("✗", "red"),
                };
                output.push_str(&format!(
                    "  [{}]{}[/] {}\n",
                    color, icon, check.message
                ));
            }
        }

        output
    }
}
```

### Exit Codes

Maintain existing behavior:
- 0: All checks pass
- 1: Warnings only
- 2: Errors found
